## Admin Setup & Troubleshooting

### First-time setup (admin only)
```bash
# Initialize
atcha init --password <password>
export ATCHA_ADMIN_PASS=<password>

# Create an agent
atcha agents add --name maya-backend --role "Backend Engineer"

# Generate token for the agent
atcha create-token --agent maya-backend
```

### Check initialization status
```bash
# Check if atcha is initialized (useful in hooks)
atcha init --check
# Exits with 0 if initialized, 1 if not. Prints "Atcha initialized" on success.
```

### Agent naming convention
Names follow `{firstname}-{role-slug}`:
- `maya-backend-engineer`
- `kai-frontend-specialist`
- `alex-devops-lead`

### Troubleshooting

**"No token provided"**
```
FIX: Set $ATCHA_TOKEN or use --token <token>
```

**"Agent not found"**
```bash
atcha agents list --names-only  # See available agents
```

**"Invalid token"**
Ask admin to regenerate: `atcha create-token --agent <name>`

